<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Sparkle appcast for Manifest (the home for finished work).

    Served at: https://procestra.app/appcast-manifest.xml
    (Manifest's SUFeedURL in Info.plist points here. On launch the app GETs
    this file and compares each <sparkle:version> against the installed
    CFBundleVersion; a higher number triggers an update prompt.)

    STATUS: Manifest is not released yet. This feed is STAGED and intentionally
    has NO <item> — Sparkle sees nothing newer, so no update is ever offered.
    That's correct until the first public build ships.

    Signing key: Manifest shares the suite EdDSA key pair by design.
    SUPublicEDKey (in Manifest's Info.plist) = moOo7kLO86SRjjyTWlHabtgP0ep5ECR7biu30ZmTwEQ=
    (Seed / Provenance / Espalier / Draught use the same key — this is intentional.)

    To ship the first version: add an <item> below with sparkle:version (the
    integer build), shortVersionString, minimumSystemVersion, a release-note
    <description>, and an <enclosure> pointing at the DMG on R2 with the
    edSignature + length from sign_update:

        .build/artifacts/sparkle/Sparkle/bin/sign_update build/Manifest-<v>.dmg
        → prints sparkle:edSignature="…" length="…"

    then deploy this file. See ../Provenance/RELEASE.md for the runbook.
-->
<rss version="2.0"
     xmlns:sparkle="http://www.andymatuschak.org/xml-namespaces/sparkle"
     xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">
    <channel>
        <title>Manifest</title>
        <link>https://procestra.app/manifest.html</link>
        <description>Updates for Manifest, the home for finished work.</description>
        <language>en</language>
        <!-- No items yet — Manifest has not shipped. Add the first <item> here at release. -->
    </channel>
</rss>
